WEBVTT

00:00:04.900 --> 00:00:07.690
<i>You'll</i> still be in school
the year after next, though.

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:17.240
What's wrong, Hana?
Something on your mind?

00:00:17.240 --> 00:00:20.160
N-No, nothing.

00:00:20.160 --> 00:00:23.460
Oho... it's <i>something</i>, all right.

00:00:23.460 --> 00:00:26.380
Does it involve that senpai of yours?

00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:28.210
N-No way!

00:00:28.210 --> 00:00:30.750
She's too easy to read.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:30.460
"Thinking about another
cooking lesson next week. OK?"
"I'll check with Mom (Read)" "Thanks"

00:00:30.750 --> 00:00:34.430
You can always open up to me, you know.

00:00:34.430 --> 00:00:39.560
Oh, please! What does a middle-schooler
know about college worries?

00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:42.310
Given your usual behavior, though,

00:00:42.310 --> 00:00:46.600
you have about a middle-schooler's
take on romance.

00:00:43.350 --> 00:00:46.770
"Uzaki-chan Wants to Hang Out!"

00:00:46.600 --> 00:00:50.480
I do not, either! Don't get smart with me!

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:52.440
And it's <i>not romance</i>!

00:00:53.940 --> 00:00:56.570
This is getting interesting, all right.

00:01:04.370 --> 00:01:07.790
"Uzaki-chan Wants to Hang Out!"

00:02:06.180 --> 00:02:10.940
"Episode 6:
Uzaki-chan Wants to Celebrate!"

00:02:27.200 --> 00:02:32.960
"Episode 7:
Uzaki-chan Wants a Confession!"

00:02:36.880 --> 00:02:40.880
Thanks, Sakurai.
You sure I can have your textbook?

00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:45.220
Sorry about all my scribbled notes--
they might make it hard to read.

00:02:45.220 --> 00:02:47.730
No, no--I'm happy to have those, too.

00:02:47.730 --> 00:02:50.230
Sakurai gets good grades, after all.

00:02:50.230 --> 00:02:54.190
Hey, are you joining the class
the next time we go out for drinks?

00:02:54.190 --> 00:02:58.110
Ooh, sorry. I can't make it. Work.

00:02:58.110 --> 00:02:59.070
Oh...

00:02:59.070 --> 00:03:01.700
But do try to come sometime, okay?

00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:03.780
Yeah... next time.

00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:05.830
I told you so.

00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:08.910
What do you mean?

00:03:08.910 --> 00:03:12.880
I was just waiting for the right moment
to launch a sneak attack on Senpai.

00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:16.090
OMG, you are <i>the best</i> at lying!

00:03:16.090 --> 00:03:19.510
Those girls are in the
same class as me and Sak.

00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:22.890
Whenever we go out,
they grumble about wanting boyfriends.

00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:24.930
They might be after Sak.

00:03:28.270 --> 00:03:30.180
Of all the ridiculous...

00:03:30.180 --> 00:03:32.770
You shouldn't assume, Sakaki.

00:03:32.770 --> 00:03:34.100
Look who's talking.

00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:39.650
I'm sure they just reached out to him
once they saw him all alone.

00:03:39.650 --> 00:03:44.740
It just means his adorable junior
isn't the only kindhearted one around.

00:03:44.740 --> 00:03:45.990
Look who's talking.

00:03:45.990 --> 00:03:51.250
And <i>that</i> means I don't have to go out
of my way to pay attention to him.

00:03:51.250 --> 00:03:53.620
What a timesaver!

00:03:53.620 --> 00:03:56.000
Yeah! It's actually a <i>good</i> thing!

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.340
So I can introduce Sak to
those girls from our class, then?

00:04:00.340 --> 00:04:01.800
That--um...

00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:05.300
That's... different.

00:04:05.300 --> 00:04:08.350
You said it yourself, Uzaki:

00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:13.140
"I have no choice but
to pay him attention."

00:04:13.140 --> 00:04:18.440
And now it's "It doesn't have
to be <i>me</i> by Sak's side"?

00:04:20.190 --> 00:04:22.320
No. No!

00:04:22.320 --> 00:04:24.910
You're forgetting something:

00:04:24.910 --> 00:04:28.910
None of those girls will
ever be that person for Senpai.

00:04:28.910 --> 00:04:30.950
That's because...

00:04:30.950 --> 00:04:33.290
...he likes <i>me</i>!

00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:35.870
Not that again!

00:04:35.870 --> 00:04:41.670
Even if those girls <i>were</i> after Senpai,
I'm the one he likes,

00:04:41.670 --> 00:04:43.670
so it's no use coming onto him.

00:04:43.670 --> 00:04:46.930
They'll just end up disappointed!

00:04:46.930 --> 00:04:51.770
Man, how pathetic would it be
to be turned down by <i>him</i>?

00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:55.060
In other words, by showering
Senpai with my attention,

00:04:55.060 --> 00:04:58.860
I'm protecting the people
around him at the same time!

00:04:58.860 --> 00:05:02.030
Such twisted logic--and so self-conscious!

00:05:02.030 --> 00:05:04.150
But...

00:05:04.150 --> 00:05:08.490
It's like you said earlier, Sakaki:
I better hurry up.

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:09.910
That's true.

00:05:09.910 --> 00:05:14.000
Honestly, that was
driven home for me earlier.

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:21.710
I mean, um... it's not like I...
didn't see it coming...

00:05:21.710 --> 00:05:23.550
Is she...?

00:05:23.550 --> 00:05:26.010
I realized something else, too:

00:05:26.010 --> 00:05:29.640
Senpai's a third-year--and
it's already December.

00:05:29.640 --> 00:05:32.260
His college years are almost over.

00:05:33.970 --> 00:05:38.850
I've got to do something
about him before graduation!

00:05:38.850 --> 00:05:40.690
That's what you meant, right?

00:05:40.690 --> 00:05:41.980
Not in the slightest!

00:05:41.980 --> 00:05:43.110
What?!

00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:46.030
You've got to make your move
before someone else does!

00:05:46.030 --> 00:05:48.320
You don't need a whole year to bag him!

00:05:48.320 --> 00:05:51.700
In fact, I'm amazed you
think it'd take that long!

00:05:51.700 --> 00:05:58.290
Sheesh... As soon as one of them
gets interested, it'll be done in a flash!

00:05:58.290 --> 00:06:02.750
Still, at least she wants
to settle this somehow.

00:06:02.750 --> 00:06:06.590
It's a big leap forward
as far as Uzaki's concerned.

00:06:06.590 --> 00:06:08.590
Anyway, there's one year left!

00:06:08.590 --> 00:06:11.930
In one year, I'll make
Senpai confess his love for me!

00:06:11.930 --> 00:06:13.720
Quit beating around the bush!

00:06:13.720 --> 00:06:18.140
Just say, "I like you," right now,
and this'll all be settled--instantly!

00:06:18.140 --> 00:06:19.770
Zip right over and do it!

00:06:19.770 --> 00:06:22.900
Wh-What?! I can't say that! No way!

00:06:22.900 --> 00:06:24.900
Why not? Say it!

00:06:24.900 --> 00:06:27.700
I'm so sick of hearing you say that!

00:06:27.700 --> 00:06:32.030
Look, <i>I</i> don't like
Senpai--<i>Senpai</i> likes <i>me</i>!

00:06:32.030 --> 00:06:35.700
Well, <i>I'm</i> sick of hearing <i>that</i>!

00:06:35.700 --> 00:06:38.790
Whatever. I'm beat.

00:06:38.790 --> 00:06:42.670
You seem ready to go for it.
I'll leave you to it.

00:06:42.670 --> 00:06:44.090
I wish you every happiness.

00:06:44.090 --> 00:06:45.750
Oh, hang on a second!

00:06:45.750 --> 00:06:47.050
What is it?

00:06:47.050 --> 00:06:51.720
What's a good way to get
Senpai to confess his love?

00:06:51.720 --> 00:06:52.970
Beats me!

00:06:59.020 --> 00:07:02.440
What's up, Itsuhito? You look tired.

00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:04.570
Don't pay it any mind.

00:07:04.570 --> 00:07:07.860
I was just giving an
acquaintance some advice.

00:07:07.860 --> 00:07:10.570
Things are moving
in the right direction...

00:07:10.570 --> 00:07:11.610
...probably.

00:07:11.610 --> 00:07:14.410
Huh.

00:07:14.410 --> 00:07:15.700
Hey, Itsuhito.

00:07:16.790 --> 00:07:20.250
Uzaki threw a birthday celebration for me.

00:07:20.250 --> 00:07:22.250
So I hear.

00:07:22.250 --> 00:07:25.790
What'd make a good
thank-you present for her...

00:07:25.790 --> 00:07:30.090
...uh, for a girl?

00:07:31.090 --> 00:07:33.800
"Bath Oil"
"Essential Lipstick"
"Shea Butter Cream" "Teddy Bear Bouquet"

00:07:34.350 --> 00:07:38.310
Sorry. I'll come up with something.

00:07:38.310 --> 00:07:42.020
Mmm. Probably for the best.

00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:44.690
Yeah, they don't need a whole year.

00:07:50.530 --> 00:07:53.950
Sakaki's no help at all.

00:07:51.780 --> 00:07:53.740
"Senpai, how's Thursday? (Read)"
"Got it--I'll check"
"Senpai, we on for tomorrow?"

00:07:53.950 --> 00:07:57.240
So what can I do over this next year...

00:07:59.660 --> 00:08:02.870
...to make Senpai admit he loves me?

00:08:12.220 --> 00:08:13.590
That's it!

00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:15.760
