00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:16.140
So listen...

00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:19.770
Senpai always grabs lunch at the
dining hall or a convenience store--

00:08:19.770 --> 00:08:22.520
what if I made him bento lunches?

00:08:22.520 --> 00:08:25.230
Is he in middle school?!
Too clingy--so cringe!

00:08:25.230 --> 00:08:26.610
What?!

00:08:26.610 --> 00:08:30.110
Whatever. You're motivated now,
so dive right on in!

00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:32.820
"Senpai, we on for tomorrow? (Read)"
"Sorry for the late reply
See you then"

00:08:30.110 --> 00:08:33.450
It's a billion times better than
your usual useless shilly-shallying!

00:08:33.450 --> 00:08:36.030
Although <i>anything</i> times
zero is still zero!

00:08:36.030 --> 00:08:41.330
Sakaki's becoming more outspoken, too.

00:08:41.330 --> 00:08:43.080
I think it's a good idea.

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:47.840
Who wouldn't love a homemade lunch
from someone like you?

00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:49.250
Right?!

00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:55.050
I already cook for him all
the time--I know what he likes.

00:08:55.050 --> 00:08:57.680
This is gonna be a slam dunk!

00:08:57.510 --> 00:09:00.140
"Easy Everyday"

00:08:58.850 --> 00:09:01.390
Or so I thought.

00:09:03.520 --> 00:09:07.020
Hup! Hup! Hup! Hup!

00:09:07.020 --> 00:09:09.860
--The whole family's staring at me.
--Hup! Hup! Hup!

00:09:09.610 --> 00:09:16.610
"Easy Everyday Bento"

00:09:09.860 --> 00:09:12.990
I get <i>you</i>, Mom, but what
about the rest of you?

00:09:12.990 --> 00:09:15.200
Go play games in your room, Yanagi.

00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:19.450
But if you won't play with me,
that leaves Kiri--

00:09:19.450 --> 00:09:23.370
and he's been turning me down
'cause I beat him so bad.

00:09:24.580 --> 00:09:28.880
Besides, I have more
fun watching you these days.

00:09:28.880 --> 00:09:31.550
Who's the bento for?

00:09:31.550 --> 00:09:36.680
You're such a good cook.
They'll be thrilled!

00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:42.310
Oh, no, don't mind me.
Go ahead with what you were doing.

00:09:42.310 --> 00:09:44.980
That's super hard to do!

00:09:44.980 --> 00:09:46.560
What's <i>your</i> deal, Kiri?

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:51.770
Don't think I'm pulling a Yanagi here.
I'm not here to tease you.

00:09:51.770 --> 00:09:53.150
Then what?

00:09:53.150 --> 00:09:56.400
I'll take care of any leftovers.
Now get to it!

00:09:56.400 --> 00:09:58.910
Back in your room, you vulture!

00:09:58.910 --> 00:10:00.490
What about you, Dad?

00:10:02.740 --> 00:10:05.160
Never mind...

00:10:05.160 --> 00:10:09.460
Who knew this family was
full of such avid rubberneckers?

00:10:09.460 --> 00:10:13.710
Tsuki remained blind
to her own love of soap operas.

00:10:15.630 --> 00:10:18.050
What should I make?

00:10:18.050 --> 00:10:22.850
A bento doesn't have to be
out of the ordinary, you know.

00:10:22.850 --> 00:10:27.480
You can use anything as long
as you avoid raw foods that spoil easily.

00:10:27.480 --> 00:10:32.230
It can be your star dish--or
whatever you yourself like.

00:10:32.230 --> 00:10:34.440
A <i>tamagoyaki</i> omelet, for sure.

00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:37.240
Yes, nice!

00:10:37.240 --> 00:10:41.490
What a real mother-daughter conversation!
This is more fun than I'd expected!

00:10:41.490 --> 00:10:43.160
Ooh, Hana! Hana!

00:10:43.160 --> 00:10:45.490
Yeah?

00:10:44.240 --> 00:10:51.080
"Pink Flaked Fish"
"For Bento Decoration"

00:10:45.490 --> 00:10:48.160
Are you <i>sure</i> you don't
want it to be heart-shaped?

00:10:48.160 --> 00:10:51.420
Yes. Now, please, Yanagi, be quiet.

00:10:51.420 --> 00:10:54.670
How about shredded
chicken breast instead of rice?

00:10:54.670 --> 00:10:56.510
Butt out, Dad!

00:10:56.510 --> 00:10:59.930
Yeah, and keep your
"advice"--I'm eating this, too!

00:10:59.930 --> 00:11:02.010
I'm not <i>making</i> any for you!

00:11:02.010 --> 00:11:03.300
Aw...

00:11:03.300 --> 00:11:05.850
Fine! I'll make enough for everybody!

00:11:05.850 --> 00:11:07.430
Yesss!

00:11:09.270 --> 00:11:14.110
I've gotta hand it to you, Mom.
Making bento is hard work.

00:11:14.110 --> 00:11:19.110
No, Hana. I don't have
everyone getting in my way.

00:11:22.280 --> 00:11:24.410
Hey.

00:11:24.410 --> 00:11:26.580
Brrr...

00:11:26.580 --> 00:11:30.000
So why'd you want to see me here--

00:11:32.420 --> 00:11:37.050
I made lunch. Just... on a whim.

00:11:37.050 --> 00:11:39.720
This is... this one's yours.

00:11:42.090 --> 00:11:45.430
Um... er... uh...

00:11:45.430 --> 00:11:50.140
What gives?
She's cooked for me plenty before...

00:11:50.140 --> 00:11:54.270
This is... kind of...

00:11:54.270 --> 00:11:57.150
Crap--is that my heart thumping?

00:11:57.150 --> 00:12:00.780
I-I mean... sorry--I--

00:12:00.780 --> 00:12:05.320
What is this? What is this--what <i>is</i> this?

00:12:05.320 --> 00:12:06.580
Thanks.

00:12:09.450 --> 00:12:11.620
Well, I'll just be going.

00:12:11.620 --> 00:12:14.170
Huh? What for?

00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:15.960
Look, it's fine.

00:12:15.960 --> 00:12:19.590
You can eat that where no one can see you.

00:12:19.590 --> 00:12:22.260
What, is the dining hall no good?

00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:24.260
It's fine!

00:12:24.260 --> 00:12:27.180
You're used to eating alone, aren't you?

00:12:27.180 --> 00:12:29.470
That's not true!

00:12:30.430 --> 00:12:33.440
I actually made myself a lunch, too...

00:12:33.440 --> 00:12:35.230
Want to eat together?

00:12:42.700 --> 00:12:44.450
Man, it's cold...

00:12:44.450 --> 00:12:47.620
What's wrong with the dining hall, anyway?

00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:58.790
Wouldn't want anyone to
see us eating matching lunches.

00:12:58.790 --> 00:13:01.260
Oh... huh.

00:13:02.460 --> 00:13:05.760
That would make sense,
yeah, if they're both the same!

00:13:05.760 --> 00:13:08.430
Why didn't <i>I</i> realize that?

00:13:08.430 --> 00:13:13.810
Turns out I didn't have a lot
of time to make them different.

00:13:13.810 --> 00:13:16.520
Sorry.

00:13:16.520 --> 00:13:19.730
Oh, hey: Drinks are on me, then.

00:13:19.730 --> 00:13:21.190
Thanks.

00:13:21.190 --> 00:13:23.990
It... It's going great!

00:13:23.990 --> 00:13:27.160
How can this be happening?

00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:31.830
Right--turns out they're
<i>both</i> middle-schoolers.

00:13:31.830 --> 00:13:35.000
Glad it turned out well this time.

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:38.080
Now for Itsuhito Sakaki's smooth exit.

00:13:38.710 --> 00:13:41.500
Meanwhile, Fujio Uzaki...

00:13:41.500 --> 00:13:42.840
Get a load of this!

00:13:42.840 --> 00:13:44.590
My daughter made this for me.

00:13:44.590 --> 00:13:46.050
Check it out!

00:13:46.050 --> 00:13:47.340
Isn't this amazing?!

00:13:47.010 --> 00:13:48.970
"November 2"

00:13:47.340 --> 00:13:49.390
Mr. Uzaki...

00:13:49.390 --> 00:13:51.470
This is not your lunch break.

00:13:51.470 --> 00:13:55.640
Please put away your lunch
and get back to work.

00:13:55.640 --> 00:14:00.230
...tickled by his daughter's homemade
bento, irritated his workplace senior.

00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:02.070
